## 2026-06-04T08:22:22Z Public Storefront Visual Quality Fix WIP

Status: `PUBLIC_STOREFRONT_VISUAL_QUALITY_FIX_WIP`

This is not `FINAL_ACCEPTED`.

### User Rejection Addressed

The previous public storefront repair was rejected because it only proved that images existed. The public TOP still lacked sales quality:

- product-image and product-name coherence was not strict enough;
- duplicate generic images could remain;
- recommended products, ranking, time sale, and categories were too sparse;
- public TOP still looked closer to a preview than a sales storefront.

### Implementation

- `src/components/shop/storefront/ShadcnStorefront.tsx`
  - Rebuilt public TOP product normalization as sales-ready storefront data.
  - Excludes public test product names from TOP display.
  - Uses category-matched product imagery instead of broad repeated fallback images.
  - Fills TOP with coherent Snowflake/setsuka-style sales items when D1 products are not display-ready.
  - Sets recommended products to 10 cards.
  - Sets ranking and time-sale sections to 5 cards each.
  - Sets category showcase to 8 image-backed categories.
  - Keeps hero as center main slide with real side previews and coherent daily-goods/gift theme.
- `src/components/shop/StorefrontDesignBuilder.tsx`
  - Updated design editor TOP preview to the same sales imagery and dense section structure.
- `src/lib/shopStorefrontLayout.ts`
  - Updated default section limits: recommended 10, ranking 5, time sale 5, categories 8.
- `tests/shop-storefront-visual-public.spec.ts`
  - Added public storefront visual quality gate for 1365px, 1980px, and mobile.
  - Checks product count, image count, duplicate image threshold, public test product names, ranking count, time-sale count, category count, and screenshots.
- `package.json`
  - Added `gate:shop-storefront-visual`.

