It is not final acceptance evidence.

## Policy Fixed On 2026-06-04

The operating policy has changed.

Wrong:

- Stop deploy only because dirty UI exists.
- Hide WIP from public visual confirmation.
- Make UI protection a hard deploy gate.

Correct:

- Create rollback checkpoint first.
- Save patch and deployment state.
- Create WIP commit.
- Deploy WIP when build passes.
- Verify through public URLs.
- List and fix problems.
- Roll back to previous Worker Version or git checkpoint when WIP is bad.
- Block only final acceptance until strict checks pass.

