## Shop Design Editor Fullscreen Repair Cycle

Status: `WIP_DESIGN_EDITOR_FULLSCREEN_REPAIR_DEPLOYED_NOT_FINAL`

Cycle timestamp: `20260604T055934Z`

The previous design editor WIP was rejected because `/s/aiboux/admin/design` was still embedded inside the normal Shop admin sidebar/header. That made the central preview too narrow and caused the Amazon-style category navigation and hero layout to break visually.

Implemented repair:

- `/s/aiboux/admin/design` now renders a dedicated fullscreen editor page instead of the normal Shop admin layout.
- The normal Shop admin sidebar is not rendered on the design editor route.
- The normal Shop admin header is not rendered on the design editor route.
- A dedicated editor top bar is used.
- The editor uses left pane, central live preview, and right settings pane.
- At a 1980px viewport, the central preview is verified to be at least 1100px wide.
- Category navigation labels are kept horizontal and are not allowed to vertically fold.
- Hero side previews show actual previous/next slide images from `/shop/design/hero-*.svg` instead of gray placeholders.
- Only `TOPページ` and `商品詳細ページ` are exposed as editable pages.
- Other storefront pages remain fixed common templates and are not exposed as page-level editor targets.

Changed files:

- `src/pages/shop/settings/design.astro`
- `src/components/shop/StorefrontDesignBuilder.tsx`
- `src/lib/shopStorefrontLayout.ts`
- `tests/shop-functional-public.spec.ts`
- `public/shop/design/hero-lifestyle.svg`
- `public/shop/design/hero-daily.svg`
- `public/shop/design/hero-season.svg`
- `ops/instructions/20260604_shop_store_design_editor_top_product_only.md`
- `ops/instructions/current.md`

